6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 659, L.D. 1665, “An Act to Provide
10 Property Tax Relief to Maine Families”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in paragraph A-2 in subparagraph (1) in the first line (page
12 1, line 27 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$2,450" and inserting the following:
13 '$2,550'
14 Amend the bill in section 2 in paragraph A-2 in subparagraph (2) in the first line (page
15 1, line 28 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$3,200" and inserting the following:
16 '$3,300'
17 Amend the bill in section 2 in paragraph A-2 in subparagraph (3) in the last line (page
18 1, line 31 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "$3,250" and inserting the following:
19 '$4,050'
20 Amend the bill by inserting after section 3 the following:
21 'Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §5403, sub-§6, as repealed and replaced by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt.
22 S, §5, is amended to read:
23 6. Property tax fairness credit. For the property tax fairness credit:
24 A. Beginning in 2018 and each year thereafter ending in 2024, by the benefit base
25 amounts in section 5219‑KK, subsection 1, paragraph A‑1, subparagraphs (1) to (3),
26 except that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding section 5402,
27 subsection 1‑B, the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer Price Index
28 for the 12-month period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year divided by
29 the Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2017; and
30 B. Beginning in 2024 and each year thereafter ending in 2024, by the benefit base
31 amount in section 5219‑KK, subsection 1, paragraph A‑1, subparagraph (4), except
32 that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding section 5402, subsection 1‑B,
33 the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month
34 period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year divided by the Chained
35 Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2023; and
